## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="342f8-113">Utilice la propiedad <xref:System.ServiceModel.MessageBodyMemberAttribute.Order%2A> para especificar la ubicación de un miembro de datos en el elemento de cuerpo de SOAP.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="342f8-113">Use the <xref:System.ServiceModel.MessageBodyMemberAttribute.Order%2A> property to specify the location of a data member in the SOAP body element.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="342f8-114">No es necesario que el valor sea consecutivo, porque no representa la posición del miembro, sólo la clave de ordenación.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="342f8-114">The value is not required to be consecutive, because it does not represent the position of the member, only the sorting key.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="342f8-115">El orden de los elementos del cuerpo es alfabético de forma predeterminada.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="342f8-115">The order of the body elements is alphabetical by default.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="342f8-116">La semántica de esta propiedad es igual que la de la propiedad <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.DataMemberAttribute.Order%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="342f8-116">The semantics of this property are the same as the semantics of the <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.DataMemberAttribute.Order%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="342f8-117">El siguiente ejemplo de código utiliza la propiedad <xref:System.ServiceModel.MessageBodyMemberAttribute.Order%2A> para serializar primero el valor `sourceAccount`, segundo el valor `targetAccount` y tercero el valor `amount`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="342f8-117">The following code example uses the <xref:System.ServiceModel.MessageBodyMemberAttribute.Order%2A> property to serialize the `sourceAccount` value first, the `targetAccount` value second and the `amount` value third.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="342f8-118">Si no se utiliza la propiedad <xref:System.ServiceModel.MessageBodyMemberAttribute.Order%2A>, se serializa primero el valor `amount`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="342f8-118">If the <xref:System.ServiceModel.MessageBodyMemberAttribute.Order%2A> property is not used, the `amount` value is serialized first.</span></span>  
  
```  
[MessageContract]  
public class BankingTransaction  
{  
  [MessageHeader] public Operation operation;  
  [MessageBodyMember(Order=1)] public Account sourceAccount;  
  [MessageBodyMember(Order=2)] public Account targetAccount;  
  [MessageBodyMember(Order=3)] public int amount;  
}  
```
